<CENTER>
<H1>&nbsp;</H1>
<H1><FONT color="mediumblue">Singular Value Decomposition </FONT> </H1>
</CENTER>

<UL><UL><UL><UL><UL><UL><UL>
<H2>The final step </H2>
       <LI><FONT size=5>A technique that decomposes a given matrix into three components –&nbsp;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
        <font color="#FF0000" size="5">U, S and V.</font></LI>
       <BR><BR>
       <LI><FONT size=5><font color="#FF0000">m x n </font> content-word-transcript matrix
        <font color="#FF0000">A</font>, of rank r, can be expressed as the product:</FONT></LI>
<p align="left">
       <BR><BR>
       <FONT size=5 color="#FF0000">A = U * S * V<sup>T</sup></FONT>
       <BR><BR>
       <FONT size=5><font color="#FF0000">U</font> is <font color="#FF0000"> m x r</font> content-word matrix </FONT>
       <BR><BR>
       <FONT size=5><font color="#FF0000">S</font> is <font color="#FF0000"> r x r
       </font> diagonal matrix </FONT>
       <BR><BR>
       <FONT size=5><font color="#FF0000">V</font></FONT><FONT size=5 color="#FF0000"><sup>T</sup></FONT>
       <FONT size=5> is <font color="#FF0000"> r x n</font> transcript matrix </FONT>
</UL></UL></UL></UL></UL></UL></UL>

